  "prompt": "How do you remove your Gmail Profile picture?",
  "response": "Removing your Gmail profile picture is done through your Google account settings, not directly within Gmail. Here's how to do it:\n\n**Steps:**\n\n1.  **Go to your Google Account:** There are several ways to get there:\n\n    *   **From Gmail:** Click your profile picture in the top right corner, then click \"Manage your Google Account.\"\n    *   **Direct Link:** Go to [myaccount.google.com](myaccount.google.com).\n    *   **Google Apps Menu:** Click the Google Apps icon (usually a 3x3 grid) in the top right of Gmail, then choose \"Account.\"\n\n2.  **Navigate to \"Personal info\":** In the left-hand menu, click on \"Personal info.\"\n\n3.  **Find the \"Photo\" section:** Scroll down until you see the \"Photo\" section.  It will display your current profile picture.\n\n4.  **Remove the Picture:**\n\n    *   **Click on your current profile picture.** This will open a new window with options for managing your photo.\n\n    *   **Click \"Remove.\"**  You'll see a confirmation prompt asking if you're sure.\n\n    *   **Confirm the Removal:** Click \"Remove\" again to confirm that you want to remove your profile picture.\n\n**After removing the picture:**\n\n*   Your profile picture will be replaced with a default image, usually based on the first letter of your name.\n*   The change might not be immediate across all Google services. It may take a few minutes or even a few hours to fully propagate.\n\n**Important Notes:**\n\n*   This process removes your profile picture from your entire Google account, not just Gmail.  It will affect your picture in other Google services like YouTube, Google Drive, etc.\n*   You can always add a new picture later by following the same steps and choosing \"Add profile photo.\"\n\nLet me know if you have any other questions!\n",
